{"type":"message","id":"619e56fa","parentId":"85d6e116","timestamp":"2026-03-21T08:35:09.385Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a heartbeat/cron job trigger. The context monitor script is running. Let me check what's happening - this is likely checking context usage and potentially creating a new session if needed.\n\nLooking at the task, it seems to be a context monitor job. I should read the HEARTBEAT.md if it exists and follow it. But there's no HEARTBEAT.md mentioned in the workspace files. Let me check the context monitor script to understand what it's doing.\n\nActually, this is a cron job for context monitoring. The script being run is:\n`powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\miliger-context-manager\\scripts\\context-monitor.ps1`\n\nThis is likely checking context usage. I should run this and see what it reports. But since it's a cron job with the sessionTarget, I should probably just report the status.\n\nWait - this is a system event from a cron job. The instruction says to read HEARTBEAT.md if it exists and follow it strictly. Since there's no HEARTBEAT.md mentioned, I should check what this context monitor is doing.\n\nLet me run the context monitor script to see what it reports.","thinkingSignature":"102f5a93c721c54028a0f611340326604c0da310c3e6f2977a59baa13d676882"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5pi811poanir_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\miliger-context-manager\\scripts\\context-monitor.ps1","timeout":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":166,"output":313,"cacheRead":38931,"cacheWrite":236,"totalTokens":39646,"cost":{"input":0.0000498,"output":0.00037559999999999997,"cacheRead":0.00116793,"cacheWrite":0.000028319999999999997,"total":0.00162165}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":