{"type":"message","id":"2117e806","parentId":"2c6616ac","timestamp":"2026-03-21T08:35:56.241Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting - the session_status shows context at 21% (43k/200k), but the context-monitor script showed 80% (159502/200000 tokens). There seems to be a discrepancy.\n\nLooking at the script output more closely:\n- \"Context usage: 80% (159502/200000 tokens)\"\n\nThis might be measuring something different - perhaps the total tokens used in the session vs the context window capacity. The session_status shows 43k/200k which is 21%.\n\nGiven the cron job is running and the monitor script flagged 80%, but the actual session context is at 21%, there's a discrepancy. The context-monitor script might be measuring something else.\n\nLooking at the cron job, it's coming from session `agent:main:cron:696799cb-400f-4ac4-9393-6c861584965d` - this IS the context monitor cron job.\n\nThe script is designed to trigger at 60% but the actual session context is only at 21%. There might be a bug in the monitoring script, or it's measuring something different (perhaps total historical tokens vs context window).\n\nGiven:\n1. The cron job is running the context monitor\n2. The monitor is reporting 80% \n3. But session_status shows 21%\n\nI should note this discrepancy but also check if the automatic session switch should happen. However, looking at the session status, the actual context usage is only 21%, which is below any threshold.\n\nLet me check what the context-monitor.ps1 script actually does to understand the discrepancy.","thinkingSignature":"3ceff2330ec5f0ca6c49033ada9e013cb797b7046e8773380eb6dd553d2c7bc9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ppbvit0yhbiw_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\miliger-context-manager\\scripts\\context-monitor.ps1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":3941,"output":373,"cacheRead":38931,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43245,"cost":{"input":0.0011822999999999998,"output":0.0004476,"cacheRead":0.00116793,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00279783}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774082148568}}
{"type":"message","id":"f5594197","parentId":"2117e806","timestamp":"2026-03-21T08:35:56.249Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ppbvit0yhbiw_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Context Monitor for Windows\n# Monitors OpenClaw session context usage and alerts when threshold is reached\n\nparam(\n    [int]$Threshold = 60,\n    [string]$LogDir = \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\workspace\\logs\",\n    [string]$LogFile = \"$LogDir\\context-monitor.log\"\n)\n\n# Ensure log directory exists\nif (!(Test-Path $LogDir)) {\n    New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $LogDir -Force | Out-Null\n}\n\nfunction Write-Log($Message) {\n    $timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\"\n    \"$timestamp - $Message\" | Out-File -Append -FilePath $LogFile\n    Write-Host \"$timestamp - $Message\"\n}\n\n# Get session list to check context usage\ntry {\n    # Use .NET Process to properly separate stdout and stderr\n    $psi = New-Object System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo\n    $psi.FileName = \"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\openclaw.cmd\"\n    $psi.Arguments = \"sessions --json\"\n    $psi.RedirectStandardOutput = $true\n    $psi.RedirectStandardError = $true\n    $psi.UseShellExecute = $false\n    $psi.CreateNoWindow = $true\n    \n    $process = New-Object System.Diagnostics.Process\n    $process.StartInfo = $psi\n    $process.Start() | Out-Null\n    \n    $stdout = $process.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd()\n    $stderr = $process.StandardError.ReadToEnd()\n    $process.WaitForExit()\n    \n    if ($stdout) {\n        # Extract JSON from stdout (find content between first { and last })\n        $jsonStart = $stdout.IndexOf('{')\n        $jsonEnd = $stdout.LastIndexOf('}')\n        \n        if ($jsonStart -ge 0 -and $jsonEnd -gt $jsonStart) {\n            $jsonContent = $stdout.Substring($jsonStart, $jsonEnd - $jsonStart + 1)\n            $data = $jsonContent | ConvertFrom-Json -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n            \n            if ($data -and $data.sessions) {\n                # Find main session\n                $mainSession = $data.sessions | Where-Object { $_.key -eq 'agent:main:main' } | Select-Object -First 1\n                \n                if ($mainSession -and $mainSession.totalTokens -and $mainSession.contextTokens) {\n                    $used = $mainSession.totalTokens\n                    $total = $mainSession.contextTokens\n                    $usage = [math]::Round(($used / $total) * 100)\n                    \n                    Write-Log \"Context usage: ${usage}% (${used}/${total} tokens)\"\n                    \n                    if ($usage -ge $Threshold) {\n                        Write-Log \"WARNING: Context usage ${usage}% exceeds threshold ${Threshold}%\"\n                        \n                        # Check memory files\n                        $memoryDir = \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\"\n                        $memoryLite = \"$memoryDir\\MEMORY-LITE.md\"\n                        \n                        if (Test-Path $memoryLite) {\n                            $content = Get-Content $memoryLite -Raw -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n                            $wordCount = ($content -split '\\s+').Count\n                            Write-Log \"MEMORY-LITE.md: $wordCount words\"\n                        }\n                        \n                        Write-Log \"ALERT: Consider starting a new session to reset context\"\n                    } else {\n                        Write-Log \"Context usage normal: ${usage}%\"\n                    }\n                } else {\n                    Write-Log \"Main session found but no token info available\"\n                }\n            } else {\n                Write-Log \"No sessions data found in JSON\"\n            }\n        } else {\n            Write-Log \"Could not find JSON content in output\"\n        }\n    } else {\n        Write-Log \"No output from sessions command\"\n    }\n} catch {\n    Write-Log \"Error checking context: $_\"\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774082156246}}
{"type":"message","id":"bb412037","parentId":"f5594197","timestamp":"2026-03-21T08:36:44.675Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand - the script is checking `totalTokens` vs `contextTokens`. The script reports 80% (159502/200000 tokens), which means:\n- totalTokens: 159502\n- contextTokens: 200000\n\nBut the session_status shows 43k/200k (21%). This is confusing - there might be two different metrics being used:\n1. session_status shows current context load: 43k/200k\n2. The script shows total tokens used in session: 159502/200000\n\nThese are different metrics. The script is measuring total tokens used in the session history vs the context capacity, while session_status shows the current active context.\n\nActually wait - looking at the session_status more carefully:\n- \"Tokens: 5.1k in / 937 out\" - these are the tokens for the current turn\n- \"Context: 43k/200k (21%)\" - this is the current context window usage\n\nBut the script shows 159502 tokens - this might be the cumulative total tokens processed in the session, not the current context. Let me check if this is actually an issue or just different metrics.\n\nGiven that:\n1. The cron job is the context monitor\n2. It reports 80% based on totalTokens/contextTokens\n3. But session_status shows 21% current context\n\nThe script might be wrong, or there's a discrepancy. However, looking at the skill description, it says the automatic switch triggers at 60%. If the script is correctly detecting 80%, then according to the skill, an automatic switch should happen.\n\nBut looking at the current state:\n- Session context is at 21%\n- The monitor script might be buggy or measuring something else\n\nLet me proceed with what the session_status shows - 21% is well below any threshold. The cron job ran, checked, and reported. The alert is just a warning from the script but the actual context is fine.\n\nI should just note this and continue - no action needed since the actual context is at 21%.","thinkingSignature":"cc844a4ea062cca0b00e8500ad3bf3cbb464174bbd72cc873b7443e437dc2b27"},{"type":"text","text":"HEARTBEAT_OK\n\nContext Monitor 运行结果：\n- 监控脚本报告：80% (159,502/200,000 tokens) - 基于历史总token\n- 实际会话状态：**21%** (43k/200k) - 当前上下文使用\n\n存在数据差异：脚本测量的可能是会话累计token vs 当前上下文。实际session_status显示上下文仅21%，低于任何阈值，无需切换。\n\n📊 会话状态正常，继续工作。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":5163,"output":519,"cacheRead":38931,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44613,"cost":{"input":0.0015489,"output":0.0006228,"cacheRead":0.00116793,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0033396299999999997}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774082156249}}
